storage.name: Account

storage.name: Events
docs: Events deposited for the current block.
NOTE: The item is unbound and should therefore never be read on chain.
It could otherwise inflate the PoV size of a block.
Events have a large in-memory size. Box the events to not go out-of-memory
just in case someone still reads them from within the runtime.

storage.name: EventCount
docs: The number of events in the `Events<T>` list.

storage.name: EventTopics
docs: Mapping between a topic (represented by T::Hash) and a vector of indexes
All topic vectors have deterministic storage locations depending on the topic. This
allows light-clients to leverage the changes trie storage tracking mechanism and
in case of changes fetch the list of events of interest.
The value has the type `(BlockNumberFor<T>, EventIndex)` because if we used only just
the `EventIndex` then in case if the topic has the same contents on the next block
no notification will be triggered thus the event might be lost.

constants.name: MinimumPeriod

storage.name: InactiveIssuance

storage.name: Account
docs: The Balances pallet example of storing the balance of an account.
type AccountStore = StorageMapShim<Self::Account<Runtime>, frame_system::Provider<Runtime>, AccountId, Self::AccountData<Balance>>
You can also store the balance of an account in the `System` pallet.
But this comes with tradeoffs, storing account balances in the system pallet stores
`frame_system` data alongside the account data contrary to storing account balances in the
`Balances` pallet, which uses a `StorageMap` to store balances data only.
NOTE: This is only used in the case that this pallet is used to store balances.

storage.name: Locks

NOTE: Should only be accessed when setting, changing and freeing a lock.

storage.name: Reserves

events.name: BalanceSet

events.name: Reserved

events.name: Unreserved

events.name: Slashed

docs: Some amount was minted into an account.

events.name: Burned

events.name: Suspended

events.name: Restored

events.name: Issued

events.name: Rescinded
docs: Total issuance was decreased by `amount`, creating a debt to be balanced.

constants.name: ExistentialDeposit
docs: The minimum amount required to keep an account open. MUST BE GREATER THAN ZERO!
If you *really* need it to be zero, you can enable the feature `insecure_zero_ed` for
this pallet. However, you do so at your own risk: this will open up a major DoS vector.
In case you have multiple sources of provider references, you may also get unexpected
behaviour if you set this to zero.
Bottom line: Do yourself a favour and make it at least one!

constants.name: OperationalFeeMultiplier
docs: A fee multiplier for `Operational` extrinsics to compute "virtual tip" to boost their
This value is multiplied by the `final_fee` to obtain a "virtual tip" that is later
added to a tip component in regular `priority` calculations.
It means that a `Normal` transaction can front-run a similarly-sized `Operational`
extrinsic (with no tip), by including a tip value greater than the virtual tip.
Note that since we use `final_fee` the multiplier applies also to the regular `tip`
sent with the transaction. So, not only does the transaction get a priority bump based
on the `inclusion_fee`, but we also amplify the impact of tips applied to `Operational`

case of the need to send a high-priority signal message this block.

and to single remote consensus. If there is some other remote consensus that uses the same
bridge hub, the separate pallet instance shall be used, In `v2` we'll have all required
primitives (lane-id aka bridge-id, derived from XCM locations) to support multiple  bridges

storage.name: BookStateFor
docs: The index of the first and last (non-empty) pages.

storage.name: ServiceHead
docs: The origin at which we should begin servicing.

storage.name: Pages
docs: The map of page indices to pages.

events.name: ProcessingFailed
docs: Message discarded due to an error in the `MessageProcessor` (usually a format error).

constants.name: HeapSize
docs: The size of the page; this implies the maximum message size which can be sent.
A good value depends on the expected message sizes, their weights, the weight that is
available for processing them and the maximal needed message size. The maximal message
size is slightly lower than this as defined by [`MaxMessageLenOf`].

constants.name: MaxStale
docs: The maximum number of stale pages (i.e. of overweight messages) allowed before culling
can happen. Once there are more stale pages than this, then historical pages may be
dropped, even if they contain unprocessed overweight messages.

constants.name: ServiceWeight
docs: The amount of weight (if any) which should be provided to the message queue for
This may be legitimately `None` in the case that you will call

errors.name: NotReapable
doc: Page is not reapable because it has items remaining to be processed and is not old
enough.

errors.name: NoPage
doc: Page to be reaped does not exist.

errors.name: NoMessage
doc: The referenced message could not be found.

errors.name: AlreadyProcessed
doc: The message was already processed and cannot be processed again.

errors.name: Queued
doc: The message is queued for future execution.

errors.name: InsufficientWeight
doc: There is temporarily not enough weight to continue servicing messages.

errors.name: TemporarilyUnprocessable
doc: This message is temporarily unprocessable.
Such errors are expected, but not guaranteed, to resolve themselves eventually through
retrying.

errors.name: QueuePaused
doc: The queue is paused and no message can be executed from it.
This can change at any time and may resolve in the future by re-trying.

errors.name: RecursiveDisallowed
doc: Another call is in progress and needs to finish before this call can happen.

events.name: BatchInterrupted
docs: Batch of dispatches did not complete fully. Index of first failing dispatch given, as

events.name: BatchCompleted
docs: Batch of dispatches completed fully with no error.

events.name: BatchCompletedWithErrors
docs: Batch of dispatches completed but has errors.

events.name: ItemCompleted
docs: A single item within a Batch of dispatches has completed with no error.

events.name: ItemFailed
docs: A single item within a Batch of dispatches has completed with error.

constants.name: batched_calls_limit
docs: The limit on the number of batched calls.

errors.name: TooManyCalls
doc: Too many calls batched.

store a dispatch call for later.

`4 + sizeof((BlockNumber, Balance, AccountId))` bytes and whose key size is

constants.name: DepositFactor

This is held for adding 32 bytes more into a pre-existing storage value.

docs: The maximum amount of signatories allowed in the multisig.

errors.name: MinimumThreshold
doc: Threshold must be 2 or greater.

errors.name: AlreadyApproved
doc: Call is already approved by this signatory.

errors.name: NoApprovalsNeeded
doc: Call doesn't need any (more) approvals.

doc: There are too few signatories in the list.

errors.name: TooManySignatories
doc: There are too many signatories in the list.

errors.name: SignatoriesOutOfOrder
doc: The signatories were provided out of order; they should be ordered.

doc: The sender was contained in the other signatories; it shouldn't be.

constants.name: ProxyDepositBase

constants.name: ProxyDepositFactor
docs: The amount of currency needed per proxy added.
This is held for adding 32 bytes plus an instance of `ProxyType` more into a
pre-existing storage value. Thus, when configuring `ProxyDepositFactor` one should take
into account `32 + proxy_type.encode().len()` bytes of data.

constants.name: MaxProxies
docs: The maximum amount of proxies allowed for a single account.

constants.name: MaxPending
docs: The maximum amount of time-delayed announcements that are allowed to be pending.

errors.name: Frozen
doc: The origin account is frozen.

errors.name: InUse
doc: The asset ID is already taken.

errors.name: BadWitness
doc: Invalid witness data given.

errors.name: MinBalanceZero
doc: Minimum balance should be non-zero.

errors.name: UnavailableConsumer
doc: Unable to increment the consumer reference counters on the account. Either no provider
reference exists to allow a non-zero balance of a non-self-sufficient asset, or one
fewer then the maximum number of consumers has been reached.

errors.name: BadMetadata
doc: Invalid metadata given.

errors.name: Unapproved
doc: No approval exists that would allow the transfer.

errors.name: WouldDie
doc: The source account would not survive the transfer and it needs to stay alive.

errors.name: AlreadyExists
doc: The asset-account already exists.

errors.name: NoDeposit
doc: The asset-account doesn't have an associated deposit.

errors.name: WouldBurn
doc: The operation would result in funds being burned.

errors.name: LiveAsset
doc: The asset is a live asset and is actively being used. Usually emit for operations such
as `start_destroy` which require the asset to be in a destroying state.

errors.name: AssetNotLive
doc: The asset is not live, and likely being destroyed.

errors.name: IncorrectStatus
doc: The asset status is not the expected status.

errors.name: NotFrozen
doc: The asset should be frozen before the given operation.

errors.name: CallbackFailed
doc: Callback action resulted in error

storage.name: Pools
docs: Map from `PoolAssetId` to `PoolInfo`. This establishes whether a pool has been officially
created rather than people sending tokens directly to a pool's public account.

storage.name: NextPoolAssetId
docs: Stores the `PoolAssetId` that is going to be used for the next lp token.
This gets incremented whenever a new lp pool is created.

events.name: PoolCreated
docs: A successful call of the `CretaPool` extrinsic will create this event.

events.name: LiquidityAdded
docs: A successful call of the `AddLiquidity` extrinsic will create this event.

events.name: LiquidityRemoved
docs: A successful call of the `RemoveLiquidity` extrinsic will create this event.

events.name: SwapExecuted
docs: Assets have been converted from one to another. Both `SwapExactTokenForToken`

events.name: SwapCreditExecuted
docs: Assets have been converted from one to another.

constants.name: LPFee
docs: A % the liquidity providers will take of every swap. Represents 10ths of a percent.

constants.name: PoolSetupFee
docs: A one-time fee to setup the pool.

constants.name: PoolSetupFeeAsset
docs: Asset class from [`Config::Assets`] used to pay the [`Config::PoolSetupFee`].

constants.name: LiquidityWithdrawalFee
docs: A fee to withdraw the liquidity.

constants.name: MintMinLiquidity
docs: The minimum LP token amount that could be minted. Ameliorates rounding errors.

constants.name: MaxSwapPathLength
docs: The max number of hops in a swap.

constants.name: PalletId
docs: The pallet's id, used for deriving its sovereign account ID.

errors.name: InvalidAssetPair
doc: Provided asset pair is not supported for pool.

errors.name: PoolExists
doc: Pool already exists.

errors.name: WrongDesiredAmount
doc: Desired amount can't be zero.

errors.name: AmountOneLessThanMinimal
doc: Provided amount should be greater than or equal to the existential deposit/asset's
minimal amount.

errors.name: AmountTwoLessThanMinimal
doc: Provided amount should be greater than or equal to the existential deposit/asset's
minimal amount.

errors.name: ReserveLeftLessThanMinimal
doc: Reserve needs to always be greater than or equal to the existential deposit/asset's
minimal amount.

errors.name: AmountOutTooHigh
doc: Desired amount can't be equal to the pool reserve.

errors.name: PoolNotFound
doc: The pool doesn't exist.

errors.name: Overflow
doc: An overflow happened.

errors.name: AssetOneDepositDidNotMeetMinimum
doc: The minimal amount requirement for the first token in the pair wasn't met.

errors.name: AssetTwoDepositDidNotMeetMinimum
doc: The minimal amount requirement for the second token in the pair wasn't met.

errors.name: AssetOneWithdrawalDidNotMeetMinimum
doc: The minimal amount requirement for the first token in the pair wasn't met.

errors.name: AssetTwoWithdrawalDidNotMeetMinimum
doc: The minimal amount requirement for the second token in the pair wasn't met.

errors.name: OptimalAmountLessThanDesired
doc: Optimal calculated amount is less than desired.

errors.name: InsufficientLiquidityMinted
doc: Insufficient liquidity minted.

errors.name: ZeroLiquidity
doc: Requested liquidity can't be zero.

errors.name: ZeroAmount
doc: Amount can't be zero.

errors.name: ProvidedMinimumNotSufficientForSwap
doc: Calculated amount out is less than provided minimum amount.

errors.name: ProvidedMaximumNotSufficientForSwap
doc: Provided maximum amount is not sufficient for swap.

errors.name: InvalidPath
doc: The provided path must consists of 2 assets at least.

errors.name: NonUniquePath
doc: The provided path must consists of unique assets.

errors.name: IncorrectPoolAssetId
doc: It was not possible to get or increment the Id of the pool.

errors.name: BelowMinimum
doc: The destination account cannot exist with the swapped funds.
